title: Transcript of remarks by Acting SFH
content_text:
p>
			Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Acting Secretary 
			for Food and Health, Professor Sophia Chan, after visiting Alice Ho 
			Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital this afternoon (August 28): Reporter: (On the temporary suspension of the right of Professor Yu 
			Cheuk-man to perform complicated cardiac interventional procedures 
			in Prince of Wales Hospital.) Acting Secretary for Food and Health: This incident has come to a 
			place where there are a lot of public concerns. The Food and Health

place where there are a lot of public concerns. The Food and Health 
			Bureau is also very concerned about the incident because it now has 
			implications on clinical governance as well as risk (management) of 
			the patients. Therefore, the Chief Executive of the Hospital 
			Authority (HA), Dr Leung Pak-yin, will later announce (the setting 
			up) of an independent committee at the HA Head Office level to 
			further investigate this whole incident. We would ensure the entire

further investigate this whole incident. We would ensure the entire 
			incident is investigated in an open and fair manner. On the 
			completion of investigation, the HA will submit the report to the 
			Food and Health Bureau. We have already discussed with the HA to 
			ensure that they will complete the investigation not only in a fair
